What you need to know:

AJU chairman Thierry Siteny from Madagascar noted that these foreign countries entice the judokas with educational scholarships, citizenship, good facilities and good remunerationSiteny noted that some of these European countries “steal” judokas from Africa when they are still young after realising their potentialSiteny said Centres for Excellence and Development across Africa where potential judokas are trained as well as given educational scholarships will help arrest the trend